5000|$|An {{anti-ballistic missile}} (ABM) is a surface-to-air missile {{designed}} to counter <b>ballistic</b> <b>missiles</b> (see <b>missile</b> <b>defense).</b> <b>Ballistic</b> <b>missiles</b> {{are used to}} deliver nuclear, chemical, biological or conventional warheads in a ballistic flight trajectory. The term [...] "anti-ballistic missile" [...] is a generic term conveying a system designed to intercept and destroy any type of ballistic threat, however {{it is commonly used}} for systems specifically designed to counter intercontinental <b>ballistic</b> <b>missiles</b> (ICBMs).|$|R
